1
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:08,266
(Ploy Ying) I passed! I passed!
(Tor Prakai) Holy shit!

2
00:00:08,933 --> 00:00:10,927
You’re acting really suspicious.

3
00:00:10,927 --> 00:00:12,666
I’m keeping an eye on you.

4
00:00:14,300 --> 00:00:15,100
Ploy.

5
00:00:15,266 --> 00:00:16,100
Yes?

6
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:17,900
Do you know Guy went to audition for a series?

7
00:00:18,566 --> 00:00:20,400
Is staying with Petchprakai really that bad?

8
00:00:20,566 --> 00:00:21,700
Even though I’ve given you everything.

9
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:23,109
I taught you to sing, I taught you to dance.

10
00:00:23,109 --> 00:00:24,695
I did everything so Guy could become a great Likay hero.

11
00:00:24,695 --> 00:00:25,733
But he didn’t want it, did he?

12
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,800
I think if Guy wanted you to know,

13
00:00:29,266 --> 00:00:30,333
he would’ve told you.

14
00:00:31,766 --> 00:00:32,683
I think

15
00:00:32,683 --> 00:00:34,850
it wouldn’t hurt to apologize.

16
00:00:34,850 --> 00:00:36,158
So he’ll know

17
00:00:36,158 --> 00:00:37,933
that you actually care about him.

18
00:00:38,166 --> 00:00:39,527
Have you told your brother yet?

19
00:00:39,751 --> 00:00:41,039
I’ll prove it to him.

20
00:00:41,437 --> 00:00:42,740
That I can do it.

21
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:51,452
Everyone!

22
00:00:51,452 --> 00:00:53,597
Has everyone seen the number one trend right now?

23
00:00:53,597 --> 00:00:56,384
New series: Engineering Chaos.

24
00:00:56,384 --> 00:00:58,639
The cast has been announced.

25
00:00:58,639 --> 00:01:02,166
Of course, Nine is the lead, no doubt.

26
00:01:02,166 --> 00:01:04,413
But the uke is a newcomer.

27
00:01:04,413 --> 00:01:05,700
His name is Tor Prakai.

28
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,466
Who’s waiting for this?

29
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:08,866
Drop a comment.

30
00:01:09,206 --> 00:01:09,763
Looks so good!

31
00:01:09,763 --> 00:01:10,263
I can’t wait!

32
00:01:10,263 --> 00:01:10,820
The uke looks familiar.

33
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:11,725
Where’s Nine’s old partner?

34
00:01:11,725 --> 00:01:12,581
His old partner already terminated the contract.

35
00:01:12,581 --> 00:01:13,137
Nine is so handsome.

36
00:01:13,137 --> 00:01:14,440
Did Nine change partners?

37
00:01:14,440 --> 00:01:17,387
Just hope the new actor won’t drag him down.

38
00:01:20,305 --> 00:01:24,046
Nine.trp started following you.

39
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:27,741
Instagram: guy_blingbling

40
00:01:27,741 --> 00:01:29,252
Instagram: nine.trp

41
00:01:29,252 --> 00:01:32,147
Add to your story.

42
00:01:32,396 --> 00:01:33,565
Instagram: guy_blingbling

43
00:01:35,884 --> 00:01:36,684
What’s this?

44
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:57,166
Hey.

45
00:02:01,066 --> 00:02:02,018
How are you?

46
00:02:02,317 --> 00:02:03,650
How is it?

47
00:02:04,666 --> 00:02:06,048
Got many followers yet?

48
00:02:06,894 --> 00:02:08,333
You didn’t tell me beforehand.

49
00:02:08,766 --> 00:02:09,924
My phone is freezing.

50
00:02:10,272 --> 00:02:12,312
Here.

51
00:02:12,312 --> 00:02:13,300
You’re becoming a star with only 200 followers.

52
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:17,600
That won’t do.

53
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:22,133
Hey.

54
00:02:23,666 --> 00:02:24,466
Do you think I should take acting classes?

55
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,100
Why?

56
00:02:27,533 --> 00:02:28,533
The workshop is coming up soon.

57
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:31,333
A workshop with you.

58
00:02:33,866 --> 00:02:34,666
But you’re already good.

59
00:02:35,733 --> 00:02:37,533
Hey.

60
00:02:38,200 --> 00:02:40,100
What are you not good at?

61
00:02:40,300 --> 00:02:41,933
You’ve performed Likay before.

62
00:02:43,300 --> 00:02:44,300
You already have the basics.

63
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:49,355
It’s different.

64
00:02:50,201 --> 00:02:51,566
Basically,

65
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:07,933
I don’t want to hold you back.

66
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,300
Hey, you.

67
00:03:18,766 --> 00:03:19,866
You heard something again, didn’t you?

68
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,446
Listen to me.

69
00:03:23,441 --> 00:03:25,301
You

70
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:28,100
are the one chosen as the best fit.

71
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,566
So,

72
00:03:33,266 --> 00:03:35,666
respect yourself.

73
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,834
And respect the team’s decision too.

74
00:03:41,766 --> 00:03:42,335
Understand?

75
00:03:44,226 --> 00:03:45,033
But…

76
00:03:46,277 --> 00:03:47,461
Alright then.

77
00:03:47,909 --> 00:03:49,131
Do you know

78
00:03:49,131 --> 00:03:50,515
how much an acting course costs?

79
00:03:56,933 --> 00:03:57,733
Huh?

80
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:05,066
But if you want to learn for free,

81
00:04:05,933 --> 00:04:07,366
I might have a way.

82
00:04:08,766 --> 00:04:09,666
What do I have to do?

83
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,200
Uh…

84
00:04:14,466 --> 00:04:16,366
Take out your phone.

85
00:04:20,766 --> 00:04:23,966
Open the app you used earlier.

86
00:04:26,752 --> 00:04:28,752
Recent searches.

87
00:04:32,266 --> 00:04:33,066
Whoa!

88
00:04:35,466 --> 00:04:36,266
Hey.

89
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:38,933
If we work together and don’t follow each other,

90
00:04:39,133 --> 00:04:41,066
people will think we don’t like each other.

91
00:04:42,266 --> 00:04:43,466
Well, I really don’t.

92
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,255
Hello?

93
00:04:57,549 --> 00:04:59,337
I’d like to book a workshop room.

94
00:05:01,427 --> 00:05:02,933
I’ll be there in 15 minutes.

95
00:05:04,326 --> 00:05:05,060
Okay.

96
00:05:05,508 --> 00:05:06,166
Thank you.

97
00:05:10,246 --> 00:05:11,133
Let’s go.

98
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:12,900
Where?

99
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,500
Acting class.

100
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:16,533
Where?

101
00:05:18,133 --> 00:05:18,933
Where?

102
00:05:20,866 --> 00:05:21,800
With who?

103
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:27,000
Someone around here.

104
00:05:29,666 --> 00:05:32,100
What do you mean “around here”?

105
00:05:32,566 --> 00:05:33,566
Are you going or not?

106
00:05:35,666 --> 00:05:36,466
You coming?

107
00:05:36,966 --> 00:05:37,709
Really?

108
00:05:37,709 --> 00:05:38,209
Yeah.

109
00:05:40,666 --> 00:05:41,466
(Tor Prakai) Okay.
(Nine) Hurry up!

110
00:05:43,002 --> 00:05:44,966
Let me grab my stuff first.

111
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:57,133
Let’s go.

112
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:28,200
Hey.

113
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:30,466
Sit first.

114
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:38,300
Are you nervous?

115
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,333
No, I’m not.

116
00:07:41,547 --> 00:07:42,717
Not nervous at all.

117
00:07:43,314 --> 00:07:46,333
Then let’s start with walking.

118
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:47,255
Walking?

119
00:07:47,255 --> 00:07:47,766
Mm.

120
00:07:49,966 --> 00:07:51,866
Walk over there for me.

121
00:07:52,866 --> 00:07:54,400
Anyone can walk, right?

122
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:56,566
Here, try.

123
00:07:57,166 --> 00:07:57,966
Okay.

124
00:08:06,533 --> 00:08:08,133
Uh, hey…

125
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:09,400
Huh?

126
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:11,766
Try to be more confident.

127
00:08:12,566 --> 00:08:14,891
First of all,

128
00:08:14,891 --> 00:08:17,219
lift your chest up.

129
00:08:17,219 --> 00:08:18,933
Relax your arms.

130
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:19,800
Yeah.

131
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:23,166
Try walking using your spine.
Be more stable.

132
00:08:24,100 --> 00:08:24,900
Okay.

133
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:25,900
Now,

134
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:27,100
walk to me.

135
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,400
Come on.

136
00:08:33,066 --> 00:08:34,421
Hey, hey.

137
00:08:34,421 --> 00:08:37,166
I think you’re too stiff right now.

138
00:08:38,566 --> 00:08:40,686
Whoa, hey.

139
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:42,200
You should be more relaxed.

140
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:42,591
One.

141
00:08:42,591 --> 00:08:43,172
Two.

142
00:08:43,281 --> 00:08:43,781
Three.

143
00:08:45,218 --> 00:08:46,166
Yeah.

144
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:48,766
I think this is good.

145
00:08:49,133 --> 00:08:49,933
Really?

146
00:08:49,933 --> 00:08:50,666
Really.

147
00:08:50,666 --> 00:08:53,333
Now lift your chin a bit.

148
00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:55,133
And show some confidence.

149
00:08:55,766 --> 00:08:56,566
Yeah.

150
00:08:56,566 --> 00:08:57,500
Hey.

151
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:06,333
Next, try placing the script
on your head like this and walk.

152
00:09:14,366 --> 00:09:15,166
Whoa!

153
00:09:15,766 --> 00:09:16,566
That’s really good.

154
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:18,066
Really?

155
00:09:18,066 --> 00:09:18,566
Really.

156
00:09:18,566 --> 00:09:20,693
Do

157
00:09:20,710 --> 00:09:22,710
Re

158
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:23,963
Mi

159
00:09:23,963 --> 00:09:25,067
Fa

160
00:09:25,067 --> 00:09:26,171
So

161
00:09:26,171 --> 00:09:27,076
La

162
00:09:27,076 --> 00:09:28,280
Ti

163
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:29,633
Do

164
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:36,000
This one?

165
00:09:38,066 --> 00:09:39,066
Then I think

166
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:43,800
you should go change.

167
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,866
Being an actor is tough.

168
00:09:50,966 --> 00:09:52,563
I thought it was just acting.

169
00:09:53,011 --> 00:09:56,148
You also have to practice speaking, walking, singing.

170
00:09:57,900 --> 00:09:58,400
Hey.

171
00:09:58,947 --> 00:10:02,015
There’s more, you’ll see.

172
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:04,933
Hey.

173
00:10:05,266 --> 00:10:06,066
Hmm.

174
00:10:06,166 --> 00:10:06,690
That

175
00:10:08,929 --> 00:10:11,066
scene, is it hard?

176
00:10:11,766 --> 00:10:12,566
Which scene?

177
00:10:13,766 --> 00:10:15,601
I read the novel.

178
00:10:16,995 --> 00:10:18,054
The NC scene.

179
00:10:18,701 --> 00:10:21,184
You had one before, was it hard?

180
00:10:23,166 --> 00:10:24,166
Not really.

181
00:10:26,366 --> 00:10:27,166
But it can be.

182
00:10:28,766 --> 00:10:30,066
I think it’ll be hard

183
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,400
if we’re not close.

184
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:37,133
How close do we have to be?

185
00:10:51,300 --> 00:10:52,600
You have to trust me.

186
00:10:56,766 --> 00:10:58,533
Because I’ll trust you too.

187
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:06,900
We just have to think we’re the characters.

188
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:12,098
And trust that

189
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,971
we won’t mix personal matters into work.

190
00:11:17,666 --> 00:11:19,166
But off work…

191
00:11:20,766 --> 00:11:22,400
we’ll talk about it later.

192
00:11:27,866 --> 00:11:28,666
I’m hungry.

193
00:11:29,333 --> 00:11:30,133
Come here.

194
00:11:31,266 --> 00:11:32,266
Go change first.

195
00:11:32,766 --> 00:11:33,800
Let’s go eat.

196
00:11:34,933 --> 00:11:36,966
Is it already time for crispy pork basil?

197
00:11:38,233 --> 00:11:39,188
Mm-hmm.

198
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:57,316
What are you doing?

199
00:11:57,764 --> 00:11:58,901
Instead of practicing.

200
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:00,913
What if it hits the equipment

201
00:12:00,913 --> 00:12:02,466
and breaks it?

202
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:05,460
We just wanted to try a new opening.

203
00:12:06,007 --> 00:12:07,664
We thought the audience would like it.

204
00:12:08,866 --> 00:12:10,137
That’s shallow thinking.

205
00:12:11,182 --> 00:12:13,950
What if an accident
happens on stage? Is it worth it?

206
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:19,672
Same goes for you.

207
00:12:19,672 --> 00:12:20,914
Playing games all day.

208
00:12:20,914 --> 00:12:23,029
Have you even tested the equipment you bought?

209
00:12:23,029 --> 00:12:24,566
You’ll run into problems during the show again.

210
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:25,866
Me too?

211
00:12:26,366 --> 00:12:27,833
Ow, what happened?

212
00:12:28,281 --> 00:12:30,000
I heard the noise from the kitchen.

213
00:12:31,533 --> 00:12:32,112
Huh?

214
00:12:32,659 --> 00:12:34,649
Why the long faces?

215
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:45,866
Hello.

216
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:47,800
Yes.

217
00:12:48,248 --> 00:12:50,601
About coming in to sign the contract, right?

218
00:12:52,100 --> 00:12:52,900
Well…

219
00:12:54,566 --> 00:12:56,790
Could I have a bit more time?

220
00:12:57,288 --> 00:13:00,059
Our Likay troupe has a show right now.

221
00:13:01,452 --> 00:13:02,871
I’ll get back to you soon.

222
00:13:03,369 --> 00:13:04,174
Thank you.

223
00:13:05,369 --> 00:13:06,118
Goodbye.

224
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,948
Hey.

225
00:13:11,800 --> 00:13:14,700
So you’re going to have a movie star sister now?

226
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:15,900
Hmm.

227
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:20,166
So are you going to announce your graduation
on the Likay stage too?

228
00:13:20,266 --> 00:13:22,066
Like ATK48?

229
00:13:22,166 --> 00:13:23,366
That’s a COVID test.

230
00:13:23,666 --> 00:13:24,966
Nonsense.

231
00:13:25,866 --> 00:13:27,166
Fine, go ahead.

232
00:13:28,133 --> 00:13:29,400
So everyone will know

233
00:13:29,933 --> 00:13:31,766
that Petchprakai has no one left.

234
00:13:35,066 --> 00:13:36,834
It must be Petchprakai’s karma.

235
00:13:37,382 --> 00:13:39,251
Everyone we build ends up betraying us.

236
00:13:40,366 --> 00:13:42,213
Did you really just say “betray”?

237
00:13:44,552 --> 00:13:46,533
After everything I’ve done for Petchprakai?

238
00:13:48,266 --> 00:13:49,600
I never wanted to be a star.

239
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:51,866
I never wanted to go to Bangkok.

240
00:13:52,766 --> 00:13:53,966
Everything I did

241
00:13:54,666 --> 00:13:57,333
was just to make Petchprakai
more well-known.

242
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:03,200
Then if you didn’t want me to do it,
why didn’t you say so from the start?

243
00:14:04,866 --> 00:14:06,202
All this time,

244
00:14:06,849 --> 00:14:08,066
when you encouraged me,

245
00:14:08,900 --> 00:14:10,266
was it all fake?

246
00:14:16,166 --> 00:14:18,300
Do you really want me to act in the series?

247
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,127
Well…

248
00:14:22,023 --> 00:14:24,482
I want Ploy
to do what Ploy wants.

249
00:14:25,179 --> 00:14:25,851
But still,

250
00:14:26,398 --> 00:14:27,863
I don’t want Ploy to leave.

251
00:14:28,958 --> 00:14:30,000
I want Ploy to stay with

252
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,319
Petchprakai forever.

253
00:14:36,165 --> 00:14:38,318
I don’t know, it’s up to you.

254
00:14:38,318 --> 00:14:40,255
I don’t want to decide for you.

255
00:14:40,802 --> 00:14:44,135
Whatever path you choose,
you’ll have me.

256
00:14:44,135 --> 00:14:45,756
And Petchprakai

257
00:14:46,403 --> 00:14:47,799
will always be by your side.

258
00:14:58,966 --> 00:15:00,266
Was that too harsh?

259
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:55,200
Oh my god!

260
00:15:56,133 --> 00:15:57,200
Ow, ow, ow!

261
00:16:19,278 --> 00:16:20,000
Ouch!

262
00:16:20,004 --> 00:16:20,859
Ow!

263
00:16:21,111 --> 00:16:21,966
Ouch!

264
00:16:22,367 --> 00:16:23,023
Ugh!

265
00:16:23,023 --> 00:16:23,694
Heavy as hell.

266
00:16:23,694 --> 00:16:25,247
(Pleng Chai) Go get the rice.
(Chae) Which rice?

267
00:16:25,247 --> 00:16:26,385
Go get the rice.

268
00:16:26,385 --> 00:16:27,123
I’m hungry.

269
00:16:27,123 --> 00:16:27,929
(Pong) Ow, ow!
(Pleng Chai) Come on, get up!

270
00:16:27,929 --> 00:16:29,033
(Ping) It’s heavy.
(Pong) Wait!

271
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:30,756
Get up.

272
00:16:31,002 --> 00:16:31,808
Go, go, go!

273
00:16:31,979 --> 00:16:32,834
(Ping) Who are you kicking?
(Pleng Chai) Eat.

274
00:16:34,691 --> 00:16:35,596
Go get the rice.

275
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:38,366
Got it.

276
00:16:41,403 --> 00:16:42,457
Come on.

277
00:16:42,462 --> 00:16:43,218
Eat.

278
00:16:48,210 --> 00:16:48,947
Ready?

279
00:16:48,947 --> 00:16:49,547
Come, I’ll serve.

280
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:50,600
Here.

281
00:16:50,601 --> 00:16:51,755
(Pong) Here, here!
(Chae) Put it away!

282
00:16:52,128 --> 00:16:53,282
Give it to me, I’ll serve.

283
00:16:54,366 --> 00:16:56,066
Today we have fish.

284
00:16:57,766 --> 00:16:58,566
Hey.

285
00:17:01,065 --> 00:17:02,333
The fish isn’t even dead.

286
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:04,000
Hey.

287
00:17:05,866 --> 00:17:08,800
The fish said it wants me to eat it.

288
00:17:09,533 --> 00:17:10,333
Bullshit.

289
00:17:11,200 --> 00:17:12,866
I don’t like fish tails, you eat it.

290
00:17:14,966 --> 00:17:16,100
Hey, stop fighting.

291
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:19,266
Morning glory said it wants me to eat it too.

292
00:17:19,733 --> 00:17:20,866
Since when do vegetables talk?

293
00:17:21,166 --> 00:17:22,533
Do fish talk then?

294
00:17:23,100 --> 00:17:25,298
(Pong) Fish don’t have mouths.
(Ping) What?

295
00:17:25,298 --> 00:17:26,866
I’m already dead, I’m fried.
Already fried.

296
00:17:26,933 --> 00:17:28,166
It told me to eat it.

297
00:17:38,066 --> 00:17:38,966
Eat up.

298
00:17:51,966 --> 00:17:53,366
Doesn’t it look good?

299
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:56,966
No.

300
00:18:01,666 --> 00:18:03,066
Then eat a lot.

301
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:05,600
Big job tomorrow.

302
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:07,566
You won’t have the energy.

303
00:18:14,600 --> 00:18:15,933
Aren’t you mad at me?

304
00:18:18,366 --> 00:18:19,166
Of course I am.

305
00:18:20,700 --> 00:18:21,800
Why wouldn’t I be?

306
00:18:28,333 --> 00:18:29,725
But I understand.

307
00:18:30,471 --> 00:18:31,917
You have a lot on your mind.

308
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:38,166
Have you messaged Guy yet?

309
00:18:41,133 --> 00:18:42,200
Then why not?

310
00:18:42,966 --> 00:18:45,100
I want to focus on Petchprakai first.

311
00:18:45,933 --> 00:18:48,066
Especially with the debt deadline getting close.

312
00:18:49,066 --> 00:18:51,166
This isn’t the time to think about myself

313
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:54,700
or care about someone who isn’t with us.

314
00:18:59,566 --> 00:19:02,100
Then you should care more about the people who are still here.

315
00:19:03,266 --> 00:19:04,366
Ping Pong Chae.

316
00:19:04,533 --> 00:19:05,400
They may be weird,

317
00:19:06,533 --> 00:19:08,400
but they’re trying for us.

318
00:19:10,133 --> 00:19:11,000
And Pleng too.

319
00:19:11,933 --> 00:19:13,666
All this time it’s only been Petchprakai.

320
00:19:14,366 --> 00:19:16,566
You still haven’t even applied to school.

321
00:19:20,933 --> 00:19:22,333
I’m sorry, everyone.

322
00:19:24,533 --> 00:19:25,970
I was too afraid

323
00:19:25,970 --> 00:19:28,133
that I couldn’t protect what Father built.

324
00:19:28,766 --> 00:19:31,500
So I became too strict
and took it out on everyone.

325
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,400
I’ve really been too stressed.

326
00:19:39,166 --> 00:19:40,049
Phet.

327
00:19:40,944 --> 00:19:41,719
Our job

328
00:19:42,515 --> 00:19:44,412
is to bring happiness to others.

329
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:47,050
Then why don’t we give ourselves some happiness too?

330
00:19:52,133 --> 00:19:53,800
I want to see you happy.

331
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,866
And smile more.

332
00:19:58,700 --> 00:20:00,067
You’re always frowning.

333
00:20:00,316 --> 00:20:00,816
Smile.

334
00:20:00,816 --> 00:20:01,900
(Phet Thae) Does it hurt?
(Ploy Ying) Hey!

335
00:20:02,100 --> 00:20:02,666
Does it hurt?

336
00:20:02,666 --> 00:20:04,066
Why are you pinching me?

337
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,933
Hey, stop it.

338
00:20:07,366 --> 00:20:08,166
Smile.

339
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:09,445
Don’t stop.

340
00:20:09,694 --> 00:20:10,382
Keep smiling.

341
00:20:10,382 --> 00:20:11,100
You’re smiling now.

342
00:20:12,466 --> 00:20:13,266
What?

343
00:20:13,633 --> 00:20:14,133
Nothing.

344
00:20:14,133 --> 00:20:14,866
Eat.

345
00:20:14,866 --> 00:20:15,666
Eat what?

346
00:20:16,100 --> 00:20:16,900
Eat.

347
00:20:20,113 --> 00:20:20,869
Vegetables.

348
00:20:20,869 --> 00:20:21,724
Okay.

349
00:20:21,724 --> 00:20:22,629
Serve me some.

350
00:20:22,629 --> 00:20:23,385
I’m mad but I still want you to eat.

351
00:20:25,468 --> 00:20:26,423
Hey, you finished it all.

352
00:20:26,423 --> 00:20:28,025
(Chae) Don’t fight!
(Pong) I want the whole thing!

353
00:20:28,025 --> 00:20:28,930
No fighting.

354
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:30,985
I’m full.

355
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:39,900
The fish is gone.

356
00:21:02,077 --> 00:21:04,724
Today at 7 PM,
watch Likay Live.

357
00:21:04,724 --> 00:21:08,565
From Petchprakai Troupe.
Free of charge.

358
00:21:09,866 --> 00:21:11,300
Your Likay troupe?

359
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:14,100
Hey.

360
00:21:14,933 --> 00:21:16,600
I should get a privacy screen for nosy people.

361
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:20,400
Come on, let me see your troupe.

362
00:21:20,866 --> 00:21:22,733
It’s not mine, it’s my brother’s.

363
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:23,908
Wow.

364
00:21:24,455 --> 00:21:25,937
Why so distant?

365
00:21:26,136 --> 00:21:27,526
He’s your brother.

366
00:21:27,526 --> 00:21:29,542
You share the same DNA.

367
00:21:30,825 --> 00:21:31,903
Have you messaged him?

368
00:21:36,766 --> 00:21:37,352
Hey.

369
00:21:37,899 --> 00:21:39,250
Drop your ego.

370
00:21:40,295 --> 00:21:41,607
Message him first.

371
00:21:42,254 --> 00:21:43,401
You won’t lose face.

372
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:53,600
Hmm.

373
00:21:55,700 --> 00:21:56,500
Oops.

374
00:21:56,933 --> 00:21:57,733
Hey.

375
00:21:57,866 --> 00:21:59,566
If you ever get mad at me,

376
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:02,333
feel free to act tough.

377
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:04,700
Seeing you act stubborn like that,

378
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,500
it’s kind of cute.

379
00:22:18,290 --> 00:22:19,145
Hey.

380
00:22:21,049 --> 00:22:21,980
Are you free tonight?

381
00:22:24,530 --> 00:22:25,485
Mm.

382
00:22:39,887 --> 00:22:41,190
Company, halt!

383
00:22:42,466 --> 00:22:43,266
What the hell?

384
00:22:43,426 --> 00:22:44,281
Attention!

385
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:49,900
What are you doing?

386
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:52,533
(Ping) What are you doing?
(Chae) What are you doing?

387
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:54,000
I should be asking that.

388
00:22:54,566 --> 00:22:55,666
What are you guys doing?

389
00:22:57,133 --> 00:22:58,100
Just sitting here.

390
00:22:58,666 --> 00:22:59,466
Oops.

391
00:22:59,623 --> 00:23:00,533
(Pong) What is this?
(Chae) What is this?

392
00:23:00,533 --> 00:23:01,333
Look.

393
00:23:01,666 --> 00:23:03,100
This is the equipment for tomorrow’s live.

394
00:23:03,800 --> 00:23:05,366
When P’Phet goes live,

395
00:23:05,766 --> 00:23:06,566
this is

396
00:23:06,566 --> 00:23:07,366
the charger.

397
00:23:08,333 --> 00:23:08,900
No.

398
00:23:08,900 --> 00:23:10,000
Right? Yeah.

399
00:23:24,671 --> 00:23:25,466
Hi, P’Phet.

400
00:23:25,466 --> 00:23:26,266
(Phet Thae) Oh.
(Chae) Hello, P’Lynchee.

401
00:23:26,299 --> 00:23:28,299
(Pong) Hey, hello, P’Lynchee.
(Ping) Hello, P’Lynchee.

402
00:23:28,535 --> 00:23:29,035
P’Lynchee.

403
00:23:29,766 --> 00:23:30,566
Take a look.

404
00:23:30,567 --> 00:23:32,445
(Lynchee) P’Ploy.
(Ploy Ying) Oh.

405
00:23:32,445 --> 00:23:34,900
Lynchee, you’re here too?

406
00:23:35,266 --> 00:23:36,746
Of course.

407
00:23:37,244 --> 00:23:40,069
I just drove back
from summer classes at university.

408
00:23:40,467 --> 00:23:42,535
As soon as Father saw the Facebook post,

409
00:23:42,535 --> 00:23:43,501
he dragged me here.

410
00:23:44,466 --> 00:23:46,300
I said I’d let him watch the live,

411
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:48,900
but he insisted on sitting front row.

412
00:23:49,766 --> 00:23:50,566
Ugh.

413
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:51,500
What a headache.

414
00:23:52,366 --> 00:23:54,100
Your makeup looks so beautiful today.

415
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:55,100
Do I look good?

416
00:23:56,266 --> 00:23:57,066
Hold this first.

417
00:23:59,300 --> 00:24:01,966
Since Guy isn’t here, who’s performing?

418
00:24:03,366 --> 00:24:04,765
P’Phet.

419
00:24:05,263 --> 00:24:08,898
He’s the best in the troupe.

420
00:24:11,400 --> 00:24:14,788
So today’s cheek-kiss scene

421
00:24:14,788 --> 00:24:16,366
will be super realistic, right?

422
00:24:16,733 --> 00:24:17,533
Huh?

423
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,000
Just kidding.

424
00:24:20,697 --> 00:24:21,800
Teasing because you look pretty.

425
00:24:22,497 --> 00:24:24,815
Now I’m blushing.

426
00:24:25,711 --> 00:24:26,796
A Little Thing Called Love?

427
00:24:28,438 --> 00:24:31,688
Have you watched

428
00:24:33,380 --> 00:24:34,099
Me?

429
00:24:34,646 --> 00:24:37,315
I really like one dialogue
that Nam said.

430
00:24:42,939 --> 00:24:44,621
Nam did everything.

431
00:24:46,363 --> 00:24:49,413
Changed everything for him.

432
00:24:50,566 --> 00:24:51,366
But now,

433
00:24:52,333 --> 00:24:53,133
Nam knows.

434
00:24:54,166 --> 00:24:56,066
The most important thing

435
00:24:57,066 --> 00:24:58,900
is to tell him directly

436
00:25:00,815 --> 00:25:01,411
that

437
00:25:05,133 --> 00:25:06,677
I think it’s very real.

438
00:25:07,122 --> 00:25:07,622
Very real.

439
00:25:07,622 --> 00:25:10,229
When we like someone,

440
00:25:10,229 --> 00:25:11,463
we tend to

441
00:25:11,861 --> 00:25:14,354
do everything for them.

442
00:25:14,652 --> 00:25:15,152
But

443
00:25:15,550 --> 00:25:17,628
if we don’t tell them,

444
00:25:17,877 --> 00:25:21,281
then it’s pointless.
Don’t you think?

445
00:25:22,666 --> 00:25:23,372
Yeah.

446
00:25:25,959 --> 00:25:26,764
Lynchee,

447
00:25:27,461 --> 00:25:27,961
how did you get here?

448
00:25:28,133 --> 00:25:29,466
I walked.

449
00:25:29,733 --> 00:25:30,661
Oh.

450
00:25:30,661 --> 00:25:33,200
Came to admire Ploy.

451
00:25:34,333 --> 00:25:35,666
She’s beautiful, right?

452
00:25:38,133 --> 00:25:38,933
Mm.

453
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:43,133
She really is.

454
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:44,133
You mean Ploy?

455
00:25:44,266 --> 00:25:45,266
Mm, yeah, she’s beautiful.

456
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:47,766
You’re supposed to say Lynchee.

457
00:25:48,300 --> 00:25:48,800
Hey.

458
00:25:48,800 --> 00:25:49,534
Well…

459
00:25:49,933 --> 00:25:50,733
Not okay.

460
00:25:51,000 --> 00:25:53,066
Why are you sulking? What’s wrong?

461
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,266
You’re supposed to compliment her.

462
00:25:55,766 --> 00:25:57,166
But you asked me, so I…

463
00:26:06,566 --> 00:26:07,899
Ploy did everything.

464
00:26:08,446 --> 00:26:10,355
Changed everything just for you.

465
00:26:11,848 --> 00:26:14,540
Now Ploy knows.

466
00:26:14,888 --> 00:26:17,108
The most important thing she must do

467
00:26:17,705 --> 00:26:20,196
is to tell Phet directly

468
00:26:22,286 --> 00:26:23,735
Ploy likes you.

469
00:26:41,646 --> 00:26:44,492
♪ I’m the leading man ♪

470
00:26:45,254 --> 00:26:48,548
♪ Living in Tha Phra, Thonburi ♪

471
00:26:49,324 --> 00:26:52,270
♪ Just a poor leading man ♪

472
00:26:53,167 --> 00:26:55,933
♪ From Thonburi, Tha Phra ♪

473
00:27:03,733 --> 00:27:04,966
You can sing that too?

474
00:27:07,733 --> 00:27:10,266
Father taught this verse to me and my brother
since we were kids.

475
00:27:14,266 --> 00:27:17,166
Imagining you as a little kid practicing Likay,

476
00:27:18,666 --> 00:27:20,333
you must’ve been so cute.

477
00:27:21,766 --> 00:27:22,700
Not really.

478
00:27:24,166 --> 00:27:25,900
I wasn’t good.

479
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:28,966
P’Phet is the one who’s good at everything.

480
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:33,651
He sings well, dances well.

481
00:27:34,497 --> 00:27:36,921
He may be strict, but he’s kind.

482
00:27:37,717 --> 00:27:40,000
He always takes care of us even when he’s tired.

483
00:27:51,366 --> 00:27:52,733
Let me watch too.

484
00:28:01,207 --> 00:28:02,162
Ploy Ying is so beautiful.

485
00:28:02,162 --> 00:28:03,060
I love this pair, their voices are so sweet.

486
00:28:03,060 --> 00:28:03,820
Mommy really loves Phet Thae.

487
00:28:03,820 --> 00:28:09,398
♪ Thank you to all the fans ♪

488
00:28:09,621 --> 00:28:10,925
Phet Thae and Ploy Ying perform so well.

489
00:28:10,925 --> 00:28:11,880
I love watching Likay live.

490
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:12,736
What time does it end today?

491
00:28:12,736 --> 00:28:14,259
♪ For giving ♪

492
00:28:14,259 --> 00:28:16,458
♪ the whale ♪

493
00:28:16,458 --> 00:28:18,458
♪ today ♪

494
00:28:19,660 --> 00:28:25,293
♪ I wish you all good luck ♪

495
00:28:25,549 --> 00:28:29,141
♪ May you be happy ♪

496
00:28:29,455 --> 00:28:31,455
♪ and bright ♪

497
00:28:31,456 --> 00:28:32,958
Mommy really loves Phet Thae.

498
00:28:32,958 --> 00:28:36,289
So fun!

499
00:28:36,289 --> 00:28:37,941
Petchprakai is so entertaining.

500
00:28:37,941 --> 00:28:40,936
I love Phet Thae and Ploy Ying.

501
00:28:40,936 --> 00:28:41,891
Ploy Ying is so beautiful!

502
00:28:41,891 --> 00:28:44,505
I love this pair, their voices are so sweet.

503
00:28:44,505 --> 00:28:47,236
♪ My heart ♪

504
00:28:54,766 --> 00:28:56,982
♪ I wish you good luck ♪

505
00:28:57,866 --> 00:28:58,966
How does it go?

506
00:28:59,366 --> 00:29:00,166
Teach me.

507
00:29:01,900 --> 00:29:02,700
♪ I wish ♪

508
00:29:03,166 --> 00:29:04,333
Is this right?

509
00:29:04,966 --> 00:29:05,766
Hey.

510
00:29:05,933 --> 00:29:06,733
Hey.

511
00:29:08,966 --> 00:29:11,700
Why are you laughing at me?

512
00:29:11,868 --> 00:29:12,804
Hey.

513
00:29:13,700 --> 00:29:15,766
Why is it kind of cute?

514
00:29:18,766 --> 00:29:20,000
I’m kidding.

515
00:29:22,366 --> 00:29:23,166
Come on.

516
00:29:27,100 --> 00:29:28,011
Hey.

517
00:29:30,033 --> 00:29:31,020
Hey.

518
00:29:31,816 --> 00:29:33,962
Don’t laugh.

519
00:29:34,500 --> 00:29:35,300
Hey.

520
00:29:37,333 --> 00:29:38,133
Hey.

521
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,974
Want to watch today’s live?

522
00:29:46,974 --> 00:29:47,474
Mm.

523
00:29:47,666 --> 00:29:48,700
Let me see.

524
00:29:48,900 --> 00:29:50,266
Watch the replay.
Mm.

525
00:29:51,570 --> 00:29:52,070
Okay.

526
00:29:52,966 --> 00:29:53,759
Hey.

527
00:29:53,759 --> 00:29:55,333
Wow, Ploy is so beautiful.

528
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:56,933
Is the live clear?

529
00:29:58,166 --> 00:29:58,966
Very.

530
00:30:01,333 --> 00:30:02,357
Anyway,

531
00:30:03,153 --> 00:30:04,553
it’s getting late.

532
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:05,800
Aren’t you heading back?

533
00:30:07,066 --> 00:30:07,866
Why?

534
00:30:08,166 --> 00:30:10,800
I thought we’d go back together.

535
00:30:12,100 --> 00:30:13,181
Don’t be cheeky.

536
00:30:14,624 --> 00:30:17,133
I’m heading back, I have university tomorrow.

537
00:30:17,466 --> 00:30:18,766
Oh, university.

538
00:30:20,866 --> 00:30:21,405
So…

539
00:30:21,753 --> 00:30:25,966
are there a lot of guys with bright futures there?

540
00:30:26,666 --> 00:30:28,356
Yeah.

541
00:30:28,704 --> 00:30:33,327
Handsome ones, stylish ones, cute ones…

542
00:30:34,223 --> 00:30:34,966
a lot.

543
00:30:36,100 --> 00:30:39,933
If you don’t believe me, try it yourself.

544
00:30:47,966 --> 00:30:49,514
Maybe I will.

545
00:30:50,957 --> 00:30:52,766
I want a future too.

546
00:30:55,300 --> 00:30:56,566
I’m going.

547
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:10,900
I’ll become one of those guys with a future.

548
00:31:11,300 --> 00:31:12,500
University, watch out.

549
00:31:23,259 --> 00:31:24,114
I’m leaving.

550
00:31:27,866 --> 00:31:28,766
I’m heading out.

551
00:31:29,333 --> 00:31:30,166
Thanks a lot.

552
00:31:30,400 --> 00:31:31,566
Get home safe.

553
00:31:36,566 --> 00:31:38,333
Why come out? There are so many mosquitoes.

554
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:41,200
Come on, take a break.

555
00:31:41,966 --> 00:31:43,266
You’ve worked hard today.

556
00:31:48,966 --> 00:31:49,953
Hey, Phet.

557
00:31:50,451 --> 00:31:52,393
We made quite a lot today.

558
00:31:52,990 --> 00:31:54,718
Is it enough to pay off the debt?

559
00:31:56,366 --> 00:31:56,866
Well…

560
00:31:57,911 --> 00:32:00,731
I checked the expenses, and we’re still short.

561
00:32:01,726 --> 00:32:02,769
I think…

562
00:32:03,665 --> 00:32:05,071
if no bookings come in,

563
00:32:05,519 --> 00:32:06,801
we’ll have to go live again.

564
00:32:09,533 --> 00:32:12,766
We can go live more often, you know.

565
00:32:14,366 --> 00:32:15,866
We have the house.

566
00:32:16,933 --> 00:32:18,100
We have the equipment.

567
00:32:19,366 --> 00:32:21,400
And if we don’t want to hire many people,

568
00:32:21,933 --> 00:32:23,900
we can just perform together.

569
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:26,966
Like when we were kids.

570
00:32:30,900 --> 00:32:32,666
I don’t want to rely on you too much.

571
00:32:35,533 --> 00:32:37,166
Because if one day Ploy isn’t here,

572
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:40,600
Petchprakai has to stand on its own.

573
00:32:45,733 --> 00:32:47,133
And why wouldn’t I be here?

574
00:32:50,566 --> 00:32:53,533
I already said it during the show,

575
00:32:54,877 --> 00:32:55,716
that I

576
00:32:56,313 --> 00:32:58,584
want to be Petchprakai’s heroine forever.

577
00:33:03,933 --> 00:33:05,200
What about the series?

578
00:33:07,266 --> 00:33:10,268
You know I only wanted that

579
00:33:10,965 --> 00:33:13,694
to bring more attention to Petchprakai.

580
00:33:14,640 --> 00:33:18,931
But now I know I don’t need to do that.

581
00:33:19,727 --> 00:33:20,966
If we work together

582
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:23,666
and make Likay more accessible,

583
00:33:24,966 --> 00:33:27,200
I believe we can do it.

584
00:33:29,866 --> 00:33:33,184
And most importantly, I’ll stay here.

585
00:33:33,781 --> 00:33:34,936
Helping you

586
00:33:35,782 --> 00:33:37,452
build Petchprakai’s next chapter

587
00:33:38,099 --> 00:33:40,000
and make Father proud.

588
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:45,010
Thank you, Ploy Ying.

589
00:33:54,300 --> 00:33:55,441
And one more thing.

590
00:33:57,233 --> 00:33:58,833
I can’t act.

591
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:03,200
Acting means loving someone else.

592
00:34:07,300 --> 00:34:08,533
But the person I love

593
00:34:11,066 --> 00:34:12,166
is already here.

594
00:34:22,500 --> 00:34:23,899
I mean…

595
00:34:24,297 --> 00:34:25,583
Pleng.

596
00:34:25,583 --> 00:34:28,495
My brothers, Ping Pong Chae and all that.

597
00:34:29,540 --> 00:34:30,471
Uh…

598
00:34:31,665 --> 00:34:32,613
And…

599
00:34:43,933 --> 00:34:45,300
I love you too.

600
00:34:47,533 --> 00:34:48,333
Stay with me.

601
00:35:05,400 --> 00:35:07,300
Don’t leave Petchprakai.

602
00:35:14,500 --> 00:35:15,466
Promise me.

603
00:35:16,700 --> 00:35:17,514
Mm?

604
00:35:17,813 --> 00:35:18,899
I promise.

605
00:35:35,333 --> 00:35:39,092
This is our first live.
Stay sharp, don’t mess up.

606
00:35:39,092 --> 00:35:42,114
Most importantly, if reporters throw anything,
don’t dodge it.

607
00:35:42,114 --> 00:35:43,066
Serve it if you can.

608
00:35:43,300 --> 00:35:45,600
Got it.
We’ll serve it well.

609
00:35:45,800 --> 00:35:46,302
Great.

610
00:35:46,750 --> 00:35:47,250
Yes.

611
00:35:47,250 --> 00:35:48,014
Let’s go.

612
00:35:52,666 --> 00:35:53,466
Hey, Nine.

613
00:35:53,566 --> 00:35:54,666
Hey, long time no see.

614
00:35:54,800 --> 00:35:55,466
Hi.

615
00:35:55,466 --> 00:35:56,400
It’s been a while.

616
00:35:57,266 --> 00:35:58,234
Hey.

617
00:35:58,533 --> 00:35:59,500
Can I get a chair?

618
00:35:59,700 --> 00:36:01,229
It’s fine.

619
00:36:01,229 --> 00:36:02,566
We can sit on each other’s laps.

620
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:03,600
Hey!

621
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:09,300
Is this our new pair?

622
00:36:09,900 --> 00:36:10,700
Good-looking.

623
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:12,800
Hello.

624
00:36:12,933 --> 00:36:13,733
Hello.

625
00:36:14,300 --> 00:36:16,266
We’ll be live for about thirty minutes today.

626
00:36:16,500 --> 00:36:19,166
It’ll be about our series.

627
00:36:19,400 --> 00:36:21,400
Feel free to read any comments.

628
00:36:21,666 --> 00:36:22,258
Okay.

629
00:36:22,258 --> 00:36:22,758
Sure.

630
00:36:22,758 --> 00:36:23,258
Ready?

631
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:24,200
Ready.

632
00:36:24,333 --> 00:36:25,133
Ready?

633
00:36:25,866 --> 00:36:26,666
Ready.

634
00:36:28,666 --> 00:36:29,466
We’re ready.

635
00:36:29,900 --> 00:36:30,700
Okay.

636
00:36:32,733 --> 00:36:34,890
Hello everyone!

637
00:36:34,890 --> 00:36:37,741
Welcome to SosatSeoulsay!

638
00:36:37,741 --> 00:36:40,000
Today we’re with a new pairing.

639
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:40,910
#NineToey

640
00:36:40,910 --> 00:36:42,005
Nine has a new partner?

641
00:36:42,664 --> 00:36:43,766
Please introduce yourselves.

642
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:45,200
Hi, I’m Nine Theerapat.

643
00:36:45,266 --> 00:36:47,600
An actor from Engineering Chaos.

644
00:36:47,966 --> 00:36:48,766
Hello.

645
00:36:48,766 --> 00:36:49,951
Tor Prakai.

646
00:36:49,951 --> 00:36:50,466
Whoa!

647
00:36:50,766 --> 00:36:52,066
Guy is live with his partner.

648
00:36:52,166 --> 00:36:52,966
(Pong) Hey! Hey!
(Chae) Where?

649
00:36:54,333 --> 00:36:55,133
Hey!

650
00:36:55,266 --> 00:36:56,900
(Pleng Chai) Let me see!
(Ploy Ying) Let me see!

651
00:36:57,566 --> 00:36:58,533
Wow,

652
00:36:59,548 --> 00:37:01,548
the casting is amazing.

653
00:37:01,766 --> 00:37:02,477
What about Toey Tawan?
(Nine) I’m not nervous at all.

654
00:37:02,477 --> 00:37:05,100
We prepared very well.

655
00:37:06,866 --> 00:37:07,866
What about Guy?

656
00:37:08,600 --> 00:37:10,533
Just a little.

657
00:37:11,149 --> 00:37:13,149
Hey.

658
00:37:15,866 --> 00:37:17,998
So sweet.

659
00:37:19,900 --> 00:37:20,900
Hey, Phet.

660
00:37:24,400 --> 00:37:26,122
Aren’t you watching with us?

661
00:37:26,122 --> 00:37:26,733
Come on.

662
00:37:27,266 --> 00:37:28,066
Look.

663
00:37:29,366 --> 00:37:30,166
Nonsense.

664
00:37:38,700 --> 00:37:39,500
What the hell?

665
00:37:40,333 --> 00:37:41,133
Keep watching.

666
00:37:41,300 --> 00:37:42,100
So cute!

667
00:37:50,766 --> 00:37:52,488
I heard Nine…

668
00:37:52,488 --> 00:37:54,906
Do you think it looks forced?
(P'Seoal) Did you help select Tor Prakai?

669
00:37:54,906 --> 00:37:56,300
Can you change it in time?
(P'Seoal) Are you part of this project?

670
00:37:56,300 --> 00:37:57,156
It wasn’t just me.

671
00:37:57,156 --> 00:37:58,586
The whole team decided.

672
00:37:58,586 --> 00:38:00,800
Why change partners?
(Nine) Because he’s very dedicated.

673
00:38:02,466 --> 00:38:03,466
What about Guy?

674
00:38:03,466 --> 00:38:05,807
Bring back #NineToey!

675
00:38:12,357 --> 00:38:13,300
Bring back #NineToey!

676
00:38:13,300 --> 00:38:14,100
Guy…

677
00:38:14,100 --> 00:38:14,989
Look at him…

678
00:38:15,300 --> 00:38:16,700
Guy? Oh.

679
00:38:16,701 --> 00:38:18,066
So stiff.

680
00:38:18,066 --> 00:38:18,866
Oh.

681
00:38:18,867 --> 00:38:19,666
Poor Nine.

682
00:38:19,666 --> 00:38:20,900
That story is really fun.

683
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:22,566
I’ve finished the novel.

684
00:38:24,200 --> 00:38:27,586
Yeah, Guy finished the novel even
before casting.

685
00:38:27,586 --> 00:38:29,964
That’s why we chose him.

686
00:38:29,964 --> 00:38:32,166
He’s truly very dedicated.

687
00:38:32,300 --> 00:38:33,133
Have you read it?

688
00:38:33,500 --> 00:38:34,566
Done. Finished it.

689
00:38:35,066 --> 00:38:36,000
Very impressive.

690
00:38:36,533 --> 00:38:37,333
Yeah.

691
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:41,700
Oops.

692
00:38:42,098 --> 00:38:44,283
Nine must miss Toey a lot.
(P'Seoal) Let’s wrap it up here for today.

693
00:38:44,283 --> 00:38:46,898
The producer is so harsh for splitting them.
(P'Seoal) See you next live, bye-bye!

694
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:48,000
Bye!

695
00:38:59,733 --> 00:39:00,533
Hey.

696
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:05,766
Are you feeling better now?

697
00:39:10,900 --> 00:39:11,400
Hey.

698
00:39:11,798 --> 00:39:14,781
About the comments,don’t listen to them just yet.

699
00:39:16,373 --> 00:39:18,077
Give the fans some time.

700
00:39:18,774 --> 00:39:22,176
I believe that if they get to know you more,

701
00:39:23,022 --> 00:39:24,816
they’ll definitely come to like you.

702
00:39:29,366 --> 00:39:30,166
Just like I do.

703
00:39:34,300 --> 00:39:35,566
Thanks for the ride.

704
00:39:36,966 --> 00:39:39,066
Are you kicking me out?

705
00:39:41,866 --> 00:39:42,666
Oh.

706
00:39:44,066 --> 00:39:45,066
Alright.

707
00:39:45,366 --> 00:39:47,066
Then get some rest.

708
00:39:47,166 --> 00:39:47,966
I won’t bother you.

709
00:39:49,100 --> 00:39:50,066
See you tomorrow.

710
00:39:54,333 --> 00:39:55,362
Wait.

711
00:39:56,507 --> 00:39:57,007
Hey.

712
00:39:57,654 --> 00:39:59,622
If you want to do anything or go anywhere,

713
00:39:59,622 --> 00:40:00,702
just tell me.

714
00:40:02,693 --> 00:40:04,707
If you want to go home,

715
00:40:05,802 --> 00:40:07,082
I’ll take you.

716
00:40:13,700 --> 00:40:14,500
Thanks.

717
00:40:16,333 --> 00:40:17,333
See you tomorrow.

718
00:41:23,213 --> 00:41:27,154
Petchprakai Troupe: [Image Sent]

719
00:41:27,839 --> 00:41:29,043
Everyone did great in this live.

720
00:41:29,043 --> 00:41:30,645
Wake up early for breakfast tomorrow.

721
00:41:30,645 --> 00:41:32,247
I want omakase for breakfast!

722
00:41:32,247 --> 00:41:33,549
Gossiping again, huh?

723
00:41:35,672 --> 00:41:39,264
Phet.

724
00:41:59,370 --> 00:42:00,524
Hey!

725
00:42:04,655 --> 00:42:05,660
Duck, duck!

726
00:42:05,660 --> 00:42:06,615
Whoa!

727
00:42:06,615 --> 00:42:07,868
Yeah, yeah!

728
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:33,407
Ow!

729
00:42:33,407 --> 00:42:35,000
Has anyone seen a comb?

730
00:42:35,266 --> 00:42:36,066
Over here!

731
00:42:38,066 --> 00:42:38,866
Ow!

732
00:42:39,466 --> 00:42:40,666
Will I find it today?

733
00:42:47,166 --> 00:42:48,000
Who the hell are you?

734
00:42:48,533 --> 00:42:49,700
How did you get into my house?

735
00:42:49,900 --> 00:42:51,900
You kinda look like Pleng.

736
00:42:52,200 --> 00:42:53,733
But more… educated.

737
00:42:53,966 --> 00:42:55,100
Can’t be him.

738
00:42:56,133 --> 00:42:59,300
Or is he possessed? I need to exorcise him.

739
00:43:00,699 --> 00:43:06,591
[Chanting nonsense]

740
00:43:06,592 --> 00:43:07,733
Ow!

741
00:43:07,733 --> 00:43:09,066
I’m just going to school!

742
00:43:10,866 --> 00:43:12,632
You? Going to school?

743
00:43:12,632 --> 00:43:13,300
Yeah.

744
00:43:13,666 --> 00:43:14,566
Do you have a fever?

745
00:43:14,666 --> 00:43:15,400
Hmm?

746
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:16,366
Are you burning up?

747
00:43:16,866 --> 00:43:17,666
I don’t have a fever.

748
00:43:18,700 --> 00:43:20,303
I’m just someone with a future…

749
00:43:20,303 --> 00:43:22,733
who’s going to bring prosperity to the nation.

750
00:43:23,566 --> 00:43:24,800
Well?

751
00:43:25,933 --> 00:43:26,733
Tell me the truth.

752
00:43:27,533 --> 00:43:28,037
Well…

753
00:43:28,684 --> 00:43:31,603
Lynchee said she likes guys
with good taste and a bright future.

754
00:43:31,603 --> 00:43:32,751
And…

755
00:43:32,751 --> 00:43:34,900
I’m the one who’ll be Lynchee’s future.

756
00:43:35,266 --> 00:43:36,788
Ugh!

757
00:43:36,788 --> 00:43:38,114
Nonsense.

758
00:43:38,114 --> 00:43:39,200
(Ping) (Chae) Yuck!
(Pong) Yuck!

759
00:43:39,533 --> 00:43:40,333
That’s good.

760
00:43:41,866 --> 00:43:44,266
Education gives you knowledge.
It won’t hurt.

761
00:43:44,700 --> 00:43:46,300
So, what major are you applying for?

762
00:43:46,566 --> 00:43:47,700
Is it still open?

763
00:43:47,900 --> 00:43:48,900
I already checked.

764
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:49,966
It’s still open.

765
00:43:50,466 --> 00:43:51,266
I think…

766
00:43:51,700 --> 00:43:52,917
I’ll study Communication Arts.

767
00:43:52,917 --> 00:43:55,125
So I can use what I learn

768
00:43:55,125 --> 00:43:56,900
to develop our troupe.

769
00:44:02,700 --> 00:44:03,500
Yeah.

770
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:04,400
Wait.

771
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:05,766
Where are you all going?

772
00:44:06,666 --> 00:44:08,966
Dressed like you’re heading to Bangkok.

773
00:44:09,733 --> 00:44:10,733
We are going to Bangkok.

774
00:44:10,900 --> 00:44:11,700
Bangkok?

775
00:44:12,300 --> 00:44:12,833
I’m coming!

776
00:44:12,833 --> 00:44:13,665
Me too!

777
00:44:13,866 --> 00:44:14,666
Me too!

778
00:44:15,100 --> 00:44:15,900
Me too!

779
00:44:16,884 --> 00:44:19,166
Me too!

780
00:44:19,733 --> 00:44:20,533
We’re not going for fun.

781
00:44:21,066 --> 00:44:23,766
We’re going to cancel a contract.

782
00:44:25,766 --> 00:44:28,133
I’ve decided not to be an actor.

783
00:44:29,066 --> 00:44:31,466
I’ll stay here and perform Likay with everyone.

784
00:44:32,503 --> 00:44:34,503
Yay!

785
00:44:36,267 --> 00:44:37,172
Fabulous!

786
00:44:38,300 --> 00:44:38,800
Likay!

787
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:39,600
Performing together?

788
00:44:41,200 --> 00:44:42,000
Really?

789
00:44:43,533 --> 00:44:46,100
You can’t tease Pleng anymore.

790
00:44:50,400 --> 00:44:51,200
So annoying.

791
00:45:03,800 --> 00:45:04,733
Are you sure about this?

792
00:45:07,000 --> 00:45:08,100
Of course.

793
00:45:08,700 --> 00:45:10,166
Why else would I come here?

794
00:45:14,466 --> 00:45:15,766
Won’t they have a problem with it?

795
00:45:16,866 --> 00:45:17,588
Hmm.

796
00:45:18,136 --> 00:45:20,851
Not sure, we’ll have to talk.

797
00:45:21,448 --> 00:45:22,465
But I think…

798
00:45:22,465 --> 00:45:24,916
we might have to pay compensation.

799
00:45:26,366 --> 00:45:27,470
Hmm.

800
00:45:28,366 --> 00:45:28,949
How much?

801
00:45:29,766 --> 00:45:31,001
Don’t worry about it.

802
00:45:31,548 --> 00:45:33,480
I have my own savings.

803
00:45:33,480 --> 00:45:35,066
I’ll handle it.

804
00:45:36,266 --> 00:45:37,246
No way.

805
00:45:38,291 --> 00:45:41,166
You’re my girlfriend, I’ll take care of it.

806
00:45:43,566 --> 00:45:44,256
What?

807
00:45:44,803 --> 00:45:48,680
Since when? You haven’t even asked.

808
00:45:51,066 --> 00:45:51,866
Then…

809
00:45:55,533 --> 00:45:56,533
Khun Ploy!

810
00:45:58,766 --> 00:46:00,966
You’re Phet Thae from Petchprakai, right?

811
00:46:01,100 --> 00:46:03,766
I watched your live, it was great!

812
00:46:04,133 --> 00:46:04,933
Yes.

813
00:46:04,966 --> 00:46:07,000
Can I take a photo? I want to show my friends.

814
00:46:07,333 --> 00:46:08,266
Sure.

815
00:46:19,400 --> 00:46:21,000
Which angle? This one?

816
00:46:27,666 --> 00:46:28,466
Thank you.

817
00:46:29,366 --> 00:46:30,166
Thank you.

818
00:46:43,766 --> 00:46:45,729
Is there something you wanted to discuss today?

819
00:46:46,177 --> 00:46:47,117
Is the contract okay?

820
00:46:48,066 --> 00:46:49,490
Everything is fine.

821
00:46:49,739 --> 00:46:52,041
Thank you so much

822
00:46:52,041 --> 00:46:53,497
for giving me this opportunity.

823
00:46:53,995 --> 00:46:54,833
But…

824
00:46:56,200 --> 00:46:58,066
I have to decline.

825
00:46:58,533 --> 00:47:00,091
Why?

826
00:47:00,091 --> 00:47:01,903
I’ve planned everything.

827
00:47:01,903 --> 00:47:03,700
The investors have already signed.

828
00:47:05,166 --> 00:47:09,710
I’ve thought it over.
I prefer Likay.

829
00:47:10,357 --> 00:47:13,400
I don’t think a series suits me.

830
00:47:13,866 --> 00:47:15,296
If you don’t want to act in the series

831
00:47:15,694 --> 00:47:18,760
Then why did you audition?
You’ve wasted my time.

832
00:47:19,556 --> 00:47:20,994
The budget has already been approved.

833
00:47:21,392 --> 00:47:23,198
What am I supposed to tell them?

834
00:47:23,994 --> 00:47:25,066
It’ll make us look bad.

835
00:47:27,466 --> 00:47:29,100
So what should I do?

836
00:47:30,600 --> 00:47:33,000
Then do the series as we agreed.

837
00:47:34,266 --> 00:47:36,166
Do you have any sense of responsibility?

838
00:47:40,566 --> 00:47:41,733
What’s going on?

839
00:47:43,166 --> 00:47:45,101
She says she doesn’t want to act.

840
00:47:45,599 --> 00:47:47,664
She wants to go back to Likay.

841
00:47:47,966 --> 00:47:49,333
Then let her.

842
00:47:49,900 --> 00:47:53,533
No, we already submitted the cast list.

843
00:47:54,733 --> 00:47:55,800
Then submit a new one.

844
00:47:55,966 --> 00:47:57,900
There are hundreds who want this role.

845
00:47:58,000 --> 00:48:00,400
She can just pay the penalty.

846
00:48:01,466 --> 00:48:02,300
How much?

847
00:48:15,766 --> 00:48:18,100
Can I pay in installments?

848
00:48:18,900 --> 00:48:21,166
How can I be sure you won’t run away?

849
00:48:24,933 --> 00:48:28,399
Fine. I’ll deduct it from Tor Prakai’s pay.

850
00:48:29,245 --> 00:48:30,049
Listen.

851
00:48:30,298 --> 00:48:32,132
Tor Prakai once told me

852
00:48:32,132 --> 00:48:34,585
that Ploy Ying truly loves Likay.

853
00:48:34,585 --> 00:48:37,476
And if one day she wants to go back,

854
00:48:37,476 --> 00:48:38,381
just let her go.

855
00:48:38,381 --> 00:48:40,365
And deduct it from him instead.

856
00:48:58,700 --> 00:48:59,251
Ploy.

857
00:49:00,445 --> 00:49:01,300
How did it go?

858
00:49:02,600 --> 00:49:03,733
It’s canceled.

859
00:49:05,200 --> 00:49:05,914
Really?

860
00:49:05,914 --> 00:49:06,466
Yeah.

861
00:49:06,566 --> 00:49:07,733
Then shall we celebrate?

862
00:49:08,766 --> 00:49:09,966
Let me find a place first.

863
00:49:11,200 --> 00:49:12,666
Let’s go get something good to eat.

864
00:49:12,900 --> 00:49:13,700
Sound good?

865
00:49:16,100 --> 00:49:17,733
They didn’t say anything?

866
00:49:24,700 --> 00:49:26,656
Or was it because you told them

867
00:49:26,656 --> 00:49:28,133
you wanted to stay with me?

868
00:49:28,866 --> 00:49:31,166
You’re so full of yourself.

869
00:49:33,900 --> 00:49:34,700
Ploy.

870
00:49:50,533 --> 00:49:51,666
Can I talk to you for a moment?

871
00:49:55,733 --> 00:49:57,300
Sure. This way.

872
00:50:04,733 --> 00:50:05,700
Right here is fine.

873
00:50:15,866 --> 00:50:17,400
You’re a celebrity, right?

874
00:50:19,333 --> 00:50:20,700
I’m an actor.

875
00:50:23,600 --> 00:50:26,287
Guy told me
you two aren’t dating.

876
00:50:27,232 --> 00:50:28,550
Just co-workers.

877
00:50:37,700 --> 00:50:39,533
Can I entrust my brother to you?

878
00:50:42,533 --> 00:50:43,333
Yes.

879
00:50:45,166 --> 00:50:46,533
As for his dream,

880
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:49,566
there’s not much I can do.

881
00:50:50,933 --> 00:50:53,600
But you probably can.

882
00:50:56,933 --> 00:50:59,266
If you ever need anything,
just contact me.

883
00:51:01,166 --> 00:51:03,400
But if one day you don’t want to take care of him anymore,

884
00:51:03,866 --> 00:51:04,666
tell me.

885
00:51:06,466 --> 00:51:08,000
So I can come take him back.

886
00:51:12,566 --> 00:51:13,066
P'Phet

887
00:51:14,459 --> 00:51:16,370
I’ll take very good care of him.

888
00:51:17,266 --> 00:51:19,451
I won’t get tired of him even for a second.

889
00:51:45,066 --> 00:51:46,500
What are you doing here today?

890
00:51:47,333 --> 00:51:48,866
I came to cancel my contract.

891
00:51:49,666 --> 00:51:51,500
So you really canceled it?

892
00:51:52,166 --> 00:51:52,966
Yeah.

893
00:51:55,166 --> 00:51:58,266
The producer told me everything.

894
00:51:58,666 --> 00:51:59,849
It’s okay.

895
00:52:00,347 --> 00:52:01,669
Don’t think too much.

896
00:52:02,067 --> 00:52:05,096
I want you to go back to Petchprakai.

897
00:52:09,800 --> 00:52:12,376
I even prepared some money.

898
00:52:13,471 --> 00:52:15,000
But it’s still not enough.

899
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:17,800
Can you take this first?

900
00:52:18,000 --> 00:52:19,766
I’ll gradually pay back the rest.

901
00:52:20,100 --> 00:52:21,166
It’s okay.

902
00:52:22,166 --> 00:52:24,000
Keep it for Petchprakai.

903
00:52:24,666 --> 00:52:27,666
Use it to buy something nice
and cook for Phet.

904
00:52:28,800 --> 00:52:29,600
I’m far away.

905
00:52:30,666 --> 00:52:32,200
I probably can’t help much.

906
00:52:33,533 --> 00:52:35,078
Use this money

907
00:52:36,173 --> 00:52:37,784
to take care of everyone for me.

908
00:52:41,866 --> 00:52:42,866
Thank you.

909
00:52:44,533 --> 00:52:45,966
I should be thanking you too.

910
00:52:47,500 --> 00:52:48,748
Then I’ll keep this money

911
00:52:48,748 --> 00:52:50,966
as a fund for Petchprakai.

912
00:53:12,970 --> 00:53:17,309
♪ It must be fate ♪

913
00:53:18,241 --> 00:53:23,774
♪ That brought us together ♪

914
00:53:25,448 --> 00:53:31,081
♪ No matter the obstacles ♪

915
00:53:31,998 --> 00:53:37,979
♪ we’ll face them together ♪

916
00:53:38,851 --> 00:53:44,882
♪ Even if we fall ♪
♪ we won’t stop dreaming ♪

917
00:53:45,862 --> 00:53:49,355
♪ Walking forward together ♪

918
00:53:50,733 --> 00:53:53,989
♪ is enough ♪

919
00:54:02,666 --> 00:54:05,063
So the boss wants

920
00:54:05,411 --> 00:54:07,614
to increase it to 200,000 per month.

921
00:54:07,733 --> 00:54:08,703
I’d like to propose

922
00:54:09,051 --> 00:54:10,933
that we adjust how we promote Petchprakai.

923
00:54:11,200 --> 00:54:14,800
If we promote it as
“Vertical Likay,”

924
00:54:15,300 --> 00:54:17,200
it’ll definitely be more interesting.

925
00:54:17,666 --> 00:54:18,466
Whoa!

926
00:54:18,966 --> 00:54:20,000
Eighty thousand.

927
00:54:20,866 --> 00:54:22,900
Do you think people will like our pilot?

928
00:54:23,066 --> 00:54:25,400
But we’ve already done our best.

929
00:54:25,766 --> 00:54:28,066
is just hoping together.

930
00:54:29,466 --> 00:54:31,300
We’ll get through this together.
